        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks JSH for his address [<hi rend="italic">Address delivered in the Ipswich Museum on 9th March 1848</hi>]. Questions a sentence which implies that only the practical use of a scientific discovery makes it worth while. The instinct for truth justifies science without any practical results. Cites his work on cirripedes.</p> 
        </abstract>
